ChatGPT is an artificial intelligence chatbot developed by OpenAI and launched in Nov 2022. It is built on top of OpenAI's GPT-3 family of large language models and has been fine-tuned (an approach to transfer learning) using both supervised and reinforcement learning techniques.
Therefore, while ChatGPT's success is impressive in its own right, it may not be entirely fair to compare it directly to other social media platforms.

Moreover, ChatGPT's success in gaining 1 million users in 5 days is partly due to the fact that it was launched by OpenAI, a well-established and highly respected artificial intelligence research organization with a large following.

While social media platforms like Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and TikTok are primarily designed for people to connect and share content with one another, ChatGPT's primary purpose is to provide conversational AI services to users.
ChatGPT was designed to provide conversational AI services, and its purpose is different from that of most social media platforms.
As an AI language model, ChatGPT's success in gaining 1 million users in 5 days is certainly impressive, but it is not necessarily fair to compare it directly to other social media platforms.
